Peru Stocks: Alturas Minerals, El Brocal, Minera IRL Rio Alto

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-07-25T23:07:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/peru-stocks-alturas-el-brocal-minera-irl-panoro-rio-alto.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The  Lima  General Index rose 0.1 percent to 22,077.03. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 0.1 percent to 2,779.16.  Gold miners advanced after futures climbed to a record,
said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based brokerage Coril SAB.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, rose 6.3 percent to 17 cents.  Minera IRL
Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in
Peru, gained 4.7 percent to $1.35.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration company, climbed 2.4 percent to
$2.52.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc
producer, fell 5.6 percent to 50 soles after the metal declined
in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
